.TH "ufshcd_exec_raw_upiu_cmd" 9 "ufshcd_exec_raw_upiu_cmd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_exec_raw_upiu_cmd \- API function for sending raw upiu commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_exec_raw_upiu_cmd
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "struct utp_upiu_req *req_upiu "  ","
.BI "struct utp_upiu_req *rsp_upiu "  ","
.BI "int msgcode "  ","
.BI "u8 *desc_buff "  ","
.BI "int *buff_len "  ","
.BI "enum query_opcode desc_op "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per-adapter instance
.IP "req_upiu" 12
upiu request
.IP "rsp_upiu" 12
upiu reply - only 8 DW as we do not support scsi commands
.IP "msgcode" 12
message code, one of UPIU Transaction Codes Initiator to Target
.IP "desc_buff" 12
pointer to descriptor buffer, NULL if NA
.IP "buff_len" 12
descriptor size, 0 if NA
.IP "desc_op" 12
descriptor operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Supports UTP Transfer requests (nop and query), and UTP Task
Management requests.
It is up to the caller to fill the upiu conent properly, as it will
be copied without any further input validations.
